Making a version of another spell that just benefits some over all is a waste of a valuble change - yea I have heard the arguements, I like PoTG the way it was, I truely hope this wasn't considered as part of the rebalance of druids.<br>
<br>
Point:<br>
<br>
Mask of Hunter<br>
<br>
Mask of Stalker<br>
<br>
----- why wasn't "Mask of Hunter just made indoor/outdoor"?<br>
<br>
They made Mask of Stalker to add another spell for SoL release, instead of fixing the original.<br>
<br>
As for PoTG becoming Single Target, I would of rather had a fix done to Group PoTG first.<br>
<br>
1. Have Aegol (line) not overwrite PoTG.<br>
2. Have PoTG not overwrite Aegol (line).<br>
3. Have PoTG stack with Mark of Marzin, Druid Main skin buff has always stacked with Symbol.<br>
4. Add an Ancient Version PoTG with Increased AC/HP/Mana and added HP Regeneration and increased duration.<br>
<br>
Well to the victors have fun solo'ing, again I seen the arguements; for any raid going Druid - spending 1200 mana during a raid while bards are tapping there drums and enchanters are hasting your mind, oh so sad you had to actual sit down to med for 60 seconds. <br>
<br>
But then thats my opinion.<br>
